docs/reports/terminal/20260518-184511_evidence-registry-gc-start.log:539:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:279:- Terminal handoff rule: future larger runs should commit and push `docs/reports/terminal/*.log`; after PASS, `d` is sufficient unless the run failed or the final status is dirty.
docs/reports/terminal/20260518-184511_evidence-registry-gc-start.log:540:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:304:Merged PR #375 added `./ns terminal-finalize`, backed by `agentic_project_kit.terminal_logging.finalize_terminal_log(...)`, plus tests and documentation. The safe terminal evidence pattern is now `/tmp` log first, finalize into `docs/reports/terminal/*.log`, then stage, commit, and push. Do not commit a repo terminal log while the current process is still writing to it.
docs/reports/terminal/20260518-184511_evidence-registry-gc-start.log:541:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:306:The implementation evidence log is committed and remotely readable at `docs/reports/terminal/20260518-182435_terminal-log-finalization-guard.log`. It records targeted tests, ruff, check-docs, doctor, and `### RESULT: PASS ###`.
docs/reports/terminal/20260518-184511_evidence-registry-gc-start.log:544:docs/STATUS.md:247:- Workflow rule added: larger terminal runs should write committed logs under `docs/reports/terminal/`, allowing `d` to mean seen-and-continue after PASS without pasting terminal output.
docs/reports/terminal/20260518-184511_evidence-registry-gc-start.log:545:docs/STATUS.md:272:PR #375 added the terminal log finalization guard. Long terminal runs should tee into a temporary log outside `docs/reports/terminal/`, then finalize the completed log with `./ns terminal-finalize <tmp-log> <name>` before staging, committing, and pushing. Finalization rejects active repo-log sources and logs without an explicit PASS, FAIL, or PENDING result marker.
docs/reports/terminal/20260518-184511_evidence-registry-gc-start.log:546:docs/workflow/WORK_ORDERS.md:45:The expected branch must be a non-main slice branch. The log path must be under `docs/reports/terminal/` and must be listed in `expected_outputs`.
docs/reports/terminal/20260518-184511_evidence-registry-gc-start.log:547:docs/workflow/WORK_ORDER_TEMPLATES.md:17:- Logs must be written under `docs/reports/terminal/`.
docs/reports/terminal/20260518-184511_evidence-registry-gc-start.log:548:docs/workflow/TERMINAL_LOG_HANDOFF_RULE.md:15:- Every larger workflow block must write its complete terminal output to `docs/reports/terminal/*.log`.
docs/reports/terminal/20260518-184511_evidence-registry-gc-start.log:549:docs/workflow/TERMINAL_LOG_HANDOFF_RULE.md:37:- `./ns run-logged <name> -- <command...>`: runs a local command while teeing output into `docs/reports/terminal/*.log` and updates `LATEST_TERMINAL_LOG.txt`.
docs/reports/terminal/20260518-184511_evidence-registry-gc-start.log:550:docs/workflow/TERMINAL_LOG_HANDOFF_RULE.md:44:Commands executed through `./ns run-logged` must not use plain `test -z "$(git status --short)"` as a cleanliness gate, because `run-logged` necessarily updates `docs/reports/terminal/LATEST_TERMINAL_LOG.txt` and creates a terminal log.
docs/reports/terminal/20260518-184511_evidence-registry-gc-start.log:551:docs/workflow/TERMINAL_LOG_HANDOFF_RULE.md:54:Do not commit a repository log file while the current process is still writing to it. Long scripts must tee into a temporary log outside `docs/reports/terminal/`, then finalize the completed log into `docs/reports/terminal/*.log` with `./ns terminal-finalize <tmp-log> <name>` before staging, committing, and pushing. The finalized log must contain an explicit `### RESULT: PASS ###`, `### RESULT: FAIL ###`, or `### RESULT: PENDING ###` marker.
docs/reports/terminal/20260518-184511_evidence-registry-gc-start.log:553:docs/workflow/NO_COPY_TERMINAL_EVIDENCE.md:12:- Relevant terminal actions must write durable evidence under docs/reports/terminal or docs/reports/command_runs.
