docs/reports/terminal/20260520-discover-communication-artifact-gc.log:21:.agentic/communication_artifacts.yaml:22:    path_glob: "docs/reports/terminal/LATEST_TERMINAL_LOG.txt"
docs/reports/terminal/20260520-discover-communication-artifact-gc.log:34:docs/TEST_GATES.md:255:`./ns artifact-gc` reports transient communication artifacts without deleting them. `./ns artifact-gc --execute` removes only registered transient `.agentic/commands/current.yaml` and `.agentic/commands/current.sh` compatibility files. It must not delete `docs/reports/terminal/LATEST_TERMINAL_LOG.txt`, because that file is part of the committed terminal-evidence pointer chain.
docs/reports/terminal/20260520-discover-communication-artifact-gc.log:43:docs/workflow/COMMUNICATION_ARTIFACT_GC.md:17:- never delete `docs/reports/terminal/LATEST_TERMINAL_LOG.txt`; repair it if needed;
docs/reports/terminal/20260520-discover-communication-artifact-gc.log:45:docs/workflow/COMMUNICATION_ARTIFACT_GC.md:24:The registry covers the existing temporary and communication artifact classes currently used by the repository: `/tmp/agentic-project-kit-*.log`, `docs/reports/terminal/*.log`, `docs/reports/terminal/LATEST_TERMINAL_LOG.txt`, `docs/reports/command_runs/*.md`, `.agentic/commands/inbox/*`, and `.agentic/commands/current.*`.
docs/reports/terminal/20260520-discover-communication-artifact-gc.log:46:docs/workflow/TERMINAL_LOG_HANDOFF_RULE.md:37:- `./ns run-logged <name> -- <command...>`: runs a local command while teeing output into `docs/reports/terminal/*.log` and updates `LATEST_TERMINAL_LOG.txt`.
docs/reports/terminal/20260520-discover-communication-artifact-gc.log:47:docs/workflow/TERMINAL_LOG_HANDOFF_RULE.md:44:Commands executed through `./ns run-logged` must not use plain `test -z "$(git status --short)"` as a cleanliness gate, because `run-logged` necessarily updates `docs/reports/terminal/LATEST_TERMINAL_LOG.txt` and creates a terminal log.
