docs/reports/terminal/20260520-discover-communication-artifact-gc.log:712:docs/reports/terminal/20260518-205333_sync-diagnose-rule-evidence-governance.log:166:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:205:`./ns up` now handles no-op branches idempotently: if no PR exists and the branch has no commits ahead of main, the command reports a clean completion state instead of failing. This is part of the deterministic cleanup of recurring workflow false failures.
docs/reports/terminal/20260520-discover-communication-artifact-gc.log:713:docs/reports/terminal/20260518-205333_sync-diagnose-rule-evidence-governance.log:175:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:233:The ./ns workflow now includes a commit-guard helper that prevents accidental direct commits and PR attempts from main. If invoked on main, it stops with an instructional failure instead of allowing a non-PR direct-main path. This is part of the current standard-error cleanup before larger GUI/Cockpit work.
docs/reports/terminal/20260520-discover-communication-artifact-gc.log:714:docs/reports/terminal/20260518-205333_sync-diagnose-rule-evidence-governance.log:179:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:248:`./ns finalize-guard <branch> [marker-text]` is now available to inspect finalization branches before attempting PR creation or cleanup. Use it when a docs finalization branch may already be merged, superseded, conflicting, or effectively represented on main. This is part of the standard-error cleanup path before larger GUI/Cockpit work.
docs/reports/terminal/20260520-discover-communication-artifact-gc.log:715:docs/reports/terminal/20260518-205333_sync-diagnose-rule-evidence-governance.log:180:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:251:## Latest completed implementation slice: safe diagnostic cleanup guard
docs/reports/terminal/20260520-discover-communication-artifact-gc.log:716:docs/reports/terminal/20260518-205333_sync-diagnose-rule-evidence-governance.log:181:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:253:The workflow now includes a safe cleanup path for diagnostic evidence files. Use it before PR completion when temporary reports or copied evidence files appear in the working tree. This prevents accidental tracked deletions and avoids another recurring non-semantic FAIL state.
docs/reports/terminal/20260520-discover-communication-artifact-gc.log:717:docs/reports/terminal/20260518-205333_sync-diagnose-rule-evidence-governance.log:183:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:265:v0.3.23 control workflow consolidation is complete and merged on main. The important completed fixes are: shared `control_state` model, stop-on-fail Python slice-runner core, documented workflow control contract, target-state-aware `./ns slice-runner`, early-stop `./ns release-gate` when release metadata is missing, and automated `./ns release-prep` metadata updates for pyproject, package `__version__`, CITATION, CHANGELOG, README, STATUS, and CURRENT_HANDOFF. Next safe direction: use the new control model to harden dirty-evidence cleanup, finalize-guard machine-readable outcomes, and stale PR cleanup classification before any GUI/Cockpit expansion.
docs/reports/terminal/20260520-discover-communication-artifact-gc.log:718:docs/reports/terminal/20260518-205333_sync-diagnose-rule-evidence-governance.log:184:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:267:Evidence-cleanup guard is merged on main via PR #316. `./ns clean-evidence` is available and `./ns up` now gives a concrete repair hint for workflow-evidence dirtiness. Next safe standard-error hardening target: make `./ns finalize-guard` return clear machine-readable outcomes such as PASS_ALREADY_ON_MAIN, PASS_NOOP_BRANCH, PASS_SUPERSEDED, FAIL_CONFLICT_RELEVANT, and FAIL_NEEDS_HUMAN_REVIEW.
docs/reports/terminal/20260520-discover-communication-artifact-gc.log:719:docs/reports/terminal/20260518-205333_sync-diagnose-rule-evidence-governance.log:186:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:271:PR cleanup classification is merged on main via PR #320. `./ns pr-cleanup` is available as a read-only stale/open PR classifier. It does not close PRs automatically; it provides deterministic labels so stale or superseded PR noise can be handled deliberately. Remaining v0.3.23 hardening direction: integrate the control-state vocabulary deeper into `./ns up` and release verification, then prepare the v0.3.23 release.
docs/reports/terminal/20260520-discover-communication-artifact-gc.log:720:docs/reports/terminal/20260518-205333_sync-diagnose-rule-evidence-governance.log:188:docs/handoff/CURRENT_HANDOFF.md:275:v0.3.23 is fully closed: GitHub Release v0.3.23 exists, Zenodo version DOI `10.5281/zenodo.20261956` is verified, and DOI metadata is recorded on main via PR #325. Current main is a clean post-release state. Recommended next direction: start v0.3.24 only if it improves the same no-copy/GUI cockpit path; otherwise cut a new planning slice for how `./ns pr-cleanup`, `./ns finalize-guard`, `./ns clean-evidence`, release controls, and safe patch helpers should appear in the local Tkinter cockpit without enabling unsafe destructive defaults.
